### E-Commerce API Tests

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7000
@correlationId = {{$guid}}

### 1. Create a new product
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{correlationId}}

{
  "name": "Laptop Pro 15",
  "description": "High-performance laptop with 16GB RAM and 512GB SSD"
}

### 2. Create another product
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{$guid}}

{
  "name": "Wireless Mouse",
  "description": "Ergonomic wireless mouse with 6 buttons"
}

### 3. Create product with validation error (name too long)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{$guid}}

{
  "name": "This is a very long product name that exceeds the maximum allowed length of 200 characters which should cause a validation error and return a 400 bad request response with details about what went wrong in the validation process",
  "description": "Test product"
}

### 4. Create product with missing fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/products
Content-Type: application/json
X-Correlation-ID: {{$guid}}

{
  "name": ""
}

### 5. Get product by ID (with inventory data)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/1
X-Correlation-ID: {{$guid}}

### 6. Get non-existent product
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products/999
X-Correlation-ID: {{$guid}}

### 7. Get all products
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/products
X-Correlation-ID: {{$guid}}

### 8. Test mock inventory API directly
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/inventory/1
X-Correlation-ID: {{$guid}}
